[2026-04-18T16:15:45.799Z] [INFO]   "tool_use_result": {
[2026-04-18T16:15:45.799Z] [INFO]     "stdout": "title:\tDisable noisy Claude Code features in solve\nstate:\tDRAFT\nauthor:\tkonard (Konstantin Diachenko)\nlabels:\t\nassignees:\tkonard (Konstantin Diachenko)\nreviewers:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t1643\nurl:\thttps://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643\nadditions:\t7557\ndeletions:\t7\nauto-merge:\tdisabled\n--\n## Summary\n\nFixes #1642.\n\nThis PR makes Claude Code runs launched by `solve` quieter and more deterministic:\n\n- Adds `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` with the required quiet settings/env map and a merge helper for `~/.claude/settings.json`.\n- Verifies/merges the global Claude settings before launching Claude, preserving unrelated settings and unrelated `env` entries.\n- Forces the six required env vars into the Claude subprocess environment via `getClaudeEnv()`.\n- Bakes the same env vars and baseline `settings.json` values into both `Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile`.\n- Adds a patch changeset and a regression test wired into `npm test`.\n- Saves issue/PR data and external Claude Code documentation snapshots under `docs/case-studies/issue-1642/`.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nBefore the fix, the new focused regression failed because `getClaudeEnv()` did not force the required quiet env vars:\n\n```text\nAssertionError [ERR_ASSERTION]: getClaudeEnv should force CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1\nundefined !== '1'\n```\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs`\n- `node tests/useless-tools.test.mjs`\n- `npm test`\n- `npm run format:check`\n- `npm run lint`\n- `npm run check:duplication`\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` after removing local `node_modules/`, matching CI job order\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs`\n- `node tests/docs-validation.mjs`\n- `node --check src/solve.mjs`\n- `node --check src/hive.mjs`\n- `bash scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh`\n\n## Notes\n\nNo screenshots are included because this is runtime/Docker configuration work, not a UI change.",
