[2026-04-18T16:26:34.839Z] [INFO]         "content": "1\t## Summary\n2\t\n3\tFixes #1642.\n4\t\n5\tThis PR makes Claude Code runs launched by `solve` quieter and more deterministic:\n6\t\n7\t- Adds `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` with the required quiet settings/env map and a merge helper for `~/.claude/settings.json`.\n8\t- Verifies/merges the global Claude settings before launching Claude, preserving unrelated settings and unrelated `env` entries.\n9\t- Forces the six required env vars into the Claude subprocess environment via `getClaudeEnv()`.\n10\t- Bakes the same env vars and baseline `settings.json` values into both `Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile`.\n11\t- Adds a patch changeset and a regression test wired into `npm test`.\n12\t- Saves issue/PR data and external Claude Code documentation snapshots under `docs/case-studies/issue-1642/`.\n13\t\n14\t## Reproduction\n15\t\n16\tBefore the fix, the new focused regression failed because `getClaudeEnv()` did not force the required quiet env vars:\n17\t\n18\t```text\n19\tAssertionError [ERR_ASSERTION]: getClaudeEnv should force CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1\n20\tundefined !== '1'\n21\t```\n22\t\n23\t## Verification\n24\t\n25\t- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs`\n26\t- `node tests/useless-tools.test.mjs`\n27\t- `npm test`\n28\t- `npm run format:check`\n29\t- `npm run lint`\n30\t- `npm run check:duplication`\n31\t- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` after removing local `node_modules/`, matching CI job order\n32\t- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs`\n33\t- `node tests/docs-validation.mjs`\n34\t- `node --check src/solve.mjs`\n35\t- `node --check src/hive.mjs`\n36\t- `bash scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh`\n37\t\n38\t## Notes\n39\t\n40\tNo screenshots are included because this is runtime/Docker configuration work, not a UI change.\n41\t\n42\t"
